# Data model (Prisma, MySQL)

Authoritative schema: app/prisma/schema.prisma. Microservice has a subset in microservice/prisma/schema.prisma.

## Core entities (selected)

- Account: top-level container for budgets, categories, account registers, reoccurrences, snapshots
- User: profile + auth material (email, password) — email/password encrypted; role USER/ADMIN; membership via UserAccount
- UserAccount: per-account permissions and allowed scopes (allowedBudgetIds, allowedAccountRegisterIds)
- Budget: budgets under an Account; isDefault/isArchived flags
- AccountRegister: concrete register for an account/budget (checking, credit, loan, asset, crypto wallet)
  - Encrypted fields: name, plaidId, plaidAccessToken, walletAddress (and their hash columns)
  - Balance and configuration: creditLimit, statementAt/interval, APRs, loan metadata, minAccountBalance
  - Associations: type (AccountType), interval (Interval), entries (RegisterEntry), reoccurrences, bill profiles/instances, splits, snapshots, crypto chains/tokens, cashOnHand
- RegisterEntry: ledger entries with amount, balance, flags (projected, reconciled, pending, cleared, matched, balance-entry, manual)
  - Encrypted field: description; Plaid linkage (plaidId + hash, plaidJson)
  - Optional link to Reoccurrence and Category
- Reoccurrence: recurring schedule, amount adjustments, optional transfer register; encrypted description; splits and name aliases
- Category: hierarchical categories (self-relation parent/children). Note: unique constraint is functional at SQL level (migration comment)
- SavingsGoal: per-budget/account movement from source register to target register, priority flags, optional category
- ReconciliationPeriod + ReconciliationItem: statement reconciliation windows and cleared entries; adjustment link to a closing RegisterEntry
- Bills: BillProfile (wrapping a Reoccurrence) and BillInstance (dated obligations with status/paid linkage)
- Notifications: NotificationEvent and NotificationDismissal keyed by user/budget/kind/occurrence
- Crypto: EvmChain, CryptoRegisterChain (register ↔ chain mapping), CryptoTokenBalance (balances and USD values)
- CashOnHand: denomination counts for physical cash tied to an AccountRegister
- Logs: PlaidItem, PlaidSyncCursor, PlaidSyncLog, IntegrationAlert, IntegrationJobLog, OpenAiRequestLog
- Security keys: Rsa (rotateable keypairs)

## Enumerations

- AmountAdjustmentMode (NONE/PERCENT/FIXED), Direction (INCREASE/DECREASE)
- ReoccurrenceSplitAmountMode (FIXED/PERCENT)
- UserRole (USER/ADMIN)
- BillItemKind (BILL/INCOME/TRANSFER), BillInstanceStatus
- ReconciliationPeriodStatus (OPEN/CLOSED)

## Encryption annotations (non-exhaustive)

- User.email, User.password — /// @encrypted (email also has /// @encryption:hash(email))
- AccountRegister.name, .plaidId, .plaidAccessToken, .walletAddress — encrypted; hash columns present
- RegisterEntry.description, .plaidId — encrypted; hash column present
- Reoccurrence.description — encrypted

Use prisma-field-encryption; generated migrators live under app/prisma/reencrypt/*

## Decimal scales (examples)

- Monetary amounts typically Decimal(19,2)
- APR fields Decimal(7,5)
- Crypto display_balance Decimal(36,18), priceUsd Decimal(19,8)

## Indexing highlights

- Many composite indexes on foreign keys and status flags for performance (e.g., RegisterEntry by registerId + flags)
- Functional unique for Category is enforced in SQL migrations (not expressible in Prisma schema)
